In 1962, at the illustrious grounds of Royaumont Abbey, situated about an hour north of Paris, a colloquium was held whose attendees included some of France’s foremost philosophers and experts on cybernetics and information theory. Presenters included Giorgio de Santillana, Lucien Goldmann, Benoit Mandelbrot, Norbert Wiener, Rene de Possel, Andre Lwoff, Abraham Moles, Henryk Greniewski, Helmar Frank, Jiři Zeman, Philos. Technol. (2016) 29:269–291 DOI 10.1007/s13347-015-0205-z